  "texts": [
    "Now consider the condition thatM, σ ⊩ □ + (□ ◁ p ∧ ¬♢ ⊊ □ ◁ p).By definition of R +, this is equivalent to: for all ⟨a′, b ′ ⟩, if ∃⟨a, b⟩ ∈ σ such that ⟨a, b + |a-b| 2 ⟩ = ⟨a ′, b ′ ⟩, then M, {⟨a ′, b ′ ⟩} ⊩ □ ◁ p ∧ ¬♢ ⊊ □ ◁ p. That is in turn equivalent to: for all ⟨a, b⟩ ∈ σ, M, {⟨a, b + |a-b| 2 ⟩} ⊩ □ ◁ p ∧ ¬♢ ⊊ □ ◁ p. By Lemma 2.47, M, {⟨a, b+ |a-b| 2 ⟩} ⊩ □ ◁ p iff (a, b+ |a-b| 2) ⊆ O.",
    "Also observe that M, {⟨a, b + |a-b| 2 ⟩} ⊩ ¬♢ ⊊ □ ◁ p iff there is no (c, d) such that (a, b + |a-b| 2) ⊊ (c, d) ⊆ O.",
    "Putting all of this together with the definition of σ O from (2.3), we have M, σ ⊩ □ + (□ ◁ p ∧ ¬♢ ⊊ □ ◁ p) iff for each ⟨a, b⟩ ∈ σ, ⟨a, b + |a-b| 2 ⟩ ∈ σ O.",
    "It follows by the definition of O -in (2.4) that M, σ ⊩ □ + (□ ◁ p ∧ ¬♢ ⊊ □ ◁ p) iff σ ⊆ σ O -.Together Lemmas 2.46 and 2.48 immediately imply the following final piece of the argument.Proposition 2.49.",
    "For the formula α from Lemma 2.48 and any model M based on F, if p M ∩ RO(R) = ↓O, then ♢ ▷ α = ↓O -.Where φ:= ♢ ▷ α and ψ:= ♢ ▷ ⊤, based on the Strategy outlined above we have completed the proof that our full possibility frame F validates the formula♢ i (p ∧ ψ) → ♢ i (p ∧ φ) ∧ ♢ i (p ∧ ¬φ).From this one example of a full possibility frame whose logic is Kripkeframe inconsistent, we can easily generate continuum many others, as in Theorem 2.50."
